nt forcognitive UniversityPress\\n17 Sporns, O. et al. (2004) Organization, development and function of\\nneuroscience. We suggest that future development of\\ncomplexbrainnetworks.TrendsCogn.Sci.8,418–425\\nmethods to define cytoarchitectonic maps [23,44,111]\\n18 Bullmore,E.andSporns,O.(2009)Complexbrainnetworks:graph\\nmighteventuallysatisfactorilyaddressmanycriticalques- theoreticalanalysisofstructuralandfunctionalsystems.Nat.Rev.\\ntions regarding the functioning of large-scale network Neurosci.10,186–198\\nnodes. 19 Hagmann, P. et al. (2008) Mapping the structural core of human\\ncerebralcortex.PLoSBiol.6,e159\\nFinally,itwillbeessentialforfuturestudiestocritically\\n20 Tzourio-Mazoyer,N.etal.(2002)Automatedanatomicallabelingof\\naddress the ways in which network nodes and edges are\\nactivationsinSPMusingamacroscopicanatomicalparcellationofthe\\nconstrainedandreorganizedbylearninganddevelopment. MNIMRIsingle-subjectbrain.Neuroimage15,273–289\\nIt is to be expected that the boundaries of network nodes 21 Desikan, R.S. et al. (2006) An automated labeling system for\\nshiftwithlearningandthatprominentchangesinnetwork subdividing the human cerebral cortex on MRI scans into gyral\\nbasedregionsofinterest.Neuroimage31,968–980\\nedges are even more likely. Consideration of individual\\n22 Schleicher,A.etal.(2009)Quantitativearchitecturalanalysis:anew\\nvariability will have important implications for under-\\napproachtocorticalmapping.J.AutismDev.Disord.39,1568–1581\\nstandingthechangesinlarge-scalenetworkfunctionthat 23 Zilles,K.andAmunts,K.(2009)Receptormapping:architectureofthe\\noccur during development. In adults, some expansion of humancerebralcortex.Curr.Opin.Neurol.22,331–339\\nnode size is likely; however, changes in the strength of 24 Zalesky,A.etal.(2010)Whole-brainanatomicalnetworks:doesthe\\nchoiceofnodesmatter?Neuroimage50,970–983\\nnetworkedgesarelikelytobemostcriticalforunderstand-\\n25 Eickhoff, S.B. et al. (2005) A new SPM toolbox for combining\\ning of large-scale network changes during learning [159] probabilistic cytoarchitectonic maps and functional imaging data.\\nand development [116]. Neuroimage25,1325–1335\\n287\\n\\n\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"returncode\": 0, \"command\": \"python -c \\\"\\nimport pdfplumber\\nwith pdfplumber.open('temp/bressler2010.pdf') as pdf:\\n    # Pages 7-10 cover the core networks\\n    for i, page in enumerate(pdf.pages):\\n        if i < 6: continue\\n        if i > 10: break\\n        text = page.extract_text()\\n        if text:\\n            print(f'--- Page {i+1} ---')\\n            print(text)\\n            print()\\n\\\" 2>&1\", \"working_dir\": \"D:\\\\files\\\\demo\\\\0312-newagent\\\\agent-alpha\"}"
